It has emerged that Germany and France could use post-Brexit rules to force British Airways (BA) to split and be spun-off as a standalone airline, the Chief Executive of Ryanair has claimed. In reaction to the news, one furious Briton claimed that the UK should "exclude the EU". The Express.co.uk reader continued: "The UK still has an agreement to tender all government procurement across the EU. "Our passports are printed in France, we are having ships built in Spain etc. Exclude the EU from pitching for our tax payers cash." Before Brexit, airlines operating within the EU had to prove they were “owned and controlled” by member states. With a quarter of BA parent International Airlines Group owned by Qatar, the UK airline could be in trouble. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...